## Let's add some complexity

Create some data to plot. Let's break this down a bit. What am I trying to do?

```{r}

# First let's define a color palette we can sample from - this is only really necessary for the demo
mypal <- RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(12, "Set3")

# start with a data frame
df <- data.frame(
  lat = rnorm(100) * 2 + 41, #sampling 100 pts from a norm dist times 2 to increase the dist and shifting it by 41
  lng = rnorm(100) * 2 - 81.5, #coordinates just less specific
  size = runif(100, 5, 20),
  color = sample(mypal, 100, replace = T)
)

# then add the data frame to a leaflet map
m2 <- leaflet(df) %>% addTiles()

m2
```


What do you get? Why?
the same thing we had before, we created the data but we haven't added it to the map

How can we interrogate the properties/attributes of an object?

The `$` operator

```{r}
m2$x
```

What do the data look like?
it has the data, but we didn't tell it what to do with the data

Let's try again to visualize it. Again, break down the code first

```{r}
# first one
m2 %>% addCircleMarkers(radius = ~size, color = ~color, fill = FALSE)
#notation here uses tilda ~ assigns the variable
#all of ours look a bit diff because its random sampling

# second one
m2 %>% addCircleMarkers(radius = runif(100, 4, 10), color = c('red'))
#changed the size, ps dont have to put color in c()

```

What happened this time???

